<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-3713] test_producer_throughput is failing with compression_type=snappy</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-3713</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The failure only happens for certain message sizes and  they started after the recent change to use the default buffer size from each compression library (&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/commit/1182d61deb23b5cd86cbe462471f7df583a796e1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/commit/1182d61deb23b5cd86cbe462471f7df583a796e1&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looking at the heap dump, it seems like there is one or more memory leaks and the larger buffer size increases their impact. I found and fixed one, but still testing to see if that fixes the problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;System test results can be found here:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://confluent-kafka-system-test-results.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/2016-05-12--001.1463071628--apache--trunk--84d17bd/report.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://confluent-kafka-system-test-results.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/2016-05-12--001.1463071628--apache--trunk--84d17bd/report.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
